      "## Why We Want External Validation of Our Relationships",
      "The impulse to seek outside confirmation of a friendship is worth understanding rather than mocking. Friendships are genuinely harder to read than romantic relationships in some ways — fewer cultural milestones, less social script around them, no ceremony to mark the shift from acquaintance to friend to someone-who-matters. You feel close to someone and you hope it is mutual, but there is often no obvious checkpoint that confirms it.",
      "A friendship calculator steps into that ambiguity and produces a number. The number is arbitrary, but the desire for a number is human and makes sense. We want to know where we stand. We want some signal, however indirect, that what we feel is real and reciprocated. The calculator gives that feeling for about 90 seconds. And sometimes 90 seconds is just what you need.",
      "## What the Calculator Is Actually Doing",
