      "The second is honesty that risks the friendship. Close friends say things you might not want to hear. About a decision that seems wrong. About a pattern they've noticed in you. About a relationship you keep defending that keeps costing you. That kind of honesty is only possible when someone values the truth of your wellbeing over the short-term comfort of the relationship. It is also genuinely risky — you can lose a friend by telling them what they need to hear. People who take that risk regularly are demonstrating a level of investment that no percentage score comes close to capturing.",
